messages.body:
$SNAP the more red and the less green I see here the more bullish I get. (Which is why I won't tag the green label).

I was saying yesterday . . I don't buy the SM / communications space gains as pandemic-related one-offs. No, the pandemic precipitated a movement that was already underway: namely remote work, geographic decentralization of org entities. For reluctant adopters, the cost efficiencies of the virtual workplace have only now been driven home. It's hard to go back once you've had a taste of it.

cc $TWLO

links.title: Subsidiary of Singapore investor Capitaland could buy Stripe, Pinterest buildings for $572 million - San Francisco Business Times
links.description: Ascendas Real Estate Investment Trust announced Tuesday that it has proposed paying $572 million for two San Francisco office buildings leased to Stripe and Pinterest in the South of Market neighborhood. The REIT, which is a subsidiary of Singapore investor Capitaland, plans to acquire 510 Townsend St. and 505 Brannan St.
